              %p.arguement
                %strong> handler(eventObject)
                A function to execute each time the event is triggered.
          .longdesc
            %p
              This method is a shortcut for
              = succeed "." do
                %code .bind('focusin', handler)
            %p
              The
              %code focusin
              event is sent to an element when it, or any element inside of it, gains focus. This is distinct from the
              %a{:href => "/focus"} focus
              event in that it supports detecting the focus event on parent elements.
            %p
              This event will likely be used together with the
              %a{:href => "/focusout"} focusout
              event.
